underlying_goal: To commit a large number of staged changes into logical, separate commits.
primary_success: Successfully analyzed a large, disparate set of file changes and grouped them into two logical, well-described commits.
brief_summary: The user invoked a commit command on a large number of staged files. Claude analyzed the changes, identified several logical groups (skill refactoring, config improvements), and split them into two distinct commits. It also correctly identified and questioned remaining uncommitted files related to a previously reverted feature.
